{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"How many of you have used\nan electronic spreadsheet,"},{"time":3760,"text":"like Microsoft Excel?"},{"time":6240,"text":"Very good."},{"time":7520,"text":"Now, how many of you have run a business\nwith a spreadsheet by hand,"},{"time":12120,"text":"like my dad did for his small\nprinting business in Philadelphia?"},{"time":16160,"text":"A lot less."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17920,"text":"Well, that's the way it was done\nfor hundreds of years."},{"time":21480,"text":"In early 1978,\nI started working on an idea"},{"time":24520,"text":"that eventually became VisiCalc."},{"time":27480,"text":"And the next year it shipped"},{"time":29160,"text":"running on something new\ncalled an Apple II personal computer."},{"time":33240,"text":"You could tell that things\nhad really changed when, six years later,"},{"time":37320,"text":"the Wall Street Journal ran an editorial"},{"time":39520,"text":"that assumed you knew what VisiCalc was\nand maybe even were using it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43760,"text":"Steve Jobs back in 1990"},{"time":47160,"text":"said that \"spreadsheets\npropelled the industry forward.\""},{"time":50880,"text":"\"VisiCalc propelled the success of Apple\nmore than any other single event.\""},{"time":55440,"text":"On a more personal note,"},{"time":57600,"text":"Steve said, \"If VisiCalc had been written\nfor some other computer,"},{"time":60760,"text":"you'd be interviewing\nsomebody else right now.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":63360,"text":"So, VisiCalc was instrumental in getting\npersonal computers on business desks."},{"time":69760,"text":"How did it come about?"},{"time":71680,"text":"What was it? What did I go through\nto make it be what it was?"},{"time":75920,"text":"Well, I first learned to program\nback in 1966, when I was 15 --"},{"time":81280,"text":"just a couple months\nafter this photo was taken."},{"time":84200,"text":"Few high schoolers had access\nto computers in those days."},{"time":87560,"text":"But through luck\nand an awful lot of perseverance,"},{"time":91080,"text":"I was able to get\ncomputer time around the city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94200,"text":"After sleeping in the mud at Woodstock,\nI went off to MIT to go to college,"},{"time":99520,"text":"where to make money,\nI worked on the Multics Project."},{"time":103320,"text":"Multics was a trailblazing\ninteractive time-sharing system."},{"time":108360,"text":"Have you heard of the Linux\nand Unix operating systems?"},{"time":111560,"text":"They came from Multics."},{"time":113320,"text":"I worked on the Multics versions"},{"time":115640,"text":"of what are known\nas interpreted computer languages,"},{"time":119480,"text":"that are used by people\nin noncomputer fields"},{"time":121960,"text":"to do their calculations\nwhile seated at a computer terminal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125560,"text":"After I graduated from MIT,"},{"time":127840,"text":"I went to work for\nDigital Equipment Corporation."},{"time":131320,"text":"At DEC, I worked on software"},{"time":134520,"text":"for the new area\nof computerized typesetting."},{"time":137800,"text":"I helped newspapers\nreplace their reporters' typewriters"},{"time":142160,"text":"with computer terminals."},{"time":143880,"text":"I'd write software"},{"time":145120,"text":"and then I'd go out in the field\nto places like the Kansas City Star,"},{"time":148840,"text":"where I would train users\nand get feedback."},{"time":151280,"text":"This was real-world experience"},{"time":153160,"text":"that is quite different\nthan what I saw in the lab at MIT."}]},{"cues":[{"time":157880,"text":"After that, I was project leader"},{"time":160520,"text":"of the software for DEC's first\nword processor, again a new field."},{"time":165720,"text":"Like with typesetting, the important thing\nwas crafting a user interface"},{"time":171240,"text":"that was both natural and efficient\nfor noncomputer people to use."},{"time":176360,"text":"After I was at DEC, I went\nto work for a small company"},{"time":180360,"text":"that made microprocessor-based electronic\ncash registers for the fast-food industry."},{"time":187360,"text":"But I had always wanted to start\na company with my friend Bob Frankston"},{"time":191080,"text":"that I met on the Multics project at MIT."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193480,"text":"So I decided to go back to school to learn\nas much as I could about business."},{"time":197200,"text":"And in the fall of 1977,"},{"time":200000,"text":"I entered the MBA program\nat Harvard Business School."},{"time":203840,"text":"I was one of the few\npercentage of students"},{"time":206360,"text":"who had a background\nin computer programming."},{"time":210080,"text":"There's a picture of me from the yearbook\nsitting in the front row."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213280,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":214320,"text":"Now, at Harvard,\nwe learned by the case method."},{"time":216960,"text":"We'd do about three cases a day."},{"time":218920,"text":"Cases consist of up to a few dozen pages\ndescribing particular business situations."},{"time":225600,"text":"They often have exhibits,\nand exhibits often have words and numbers"},{"time":230200,"text":"laid out in ways that make sense\nfor the particular situation."},{"time":233840,"text":"They're usually all somewhat different."},{"time":235800,"text":"Here's my homework."},{"time":237040,"text":"Again, numbers, words,\nlaid out in ways that made sense."},{"time":240240,"text":"Lots of calculations --\nwe got really close to our calculators."},{"time":244720,"text":"In fact, here's my calculator."},{"time":248200,"text":"For Halloween, I went\ndressed up as a calculator."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":253785,"text":"At the beginning of each class,\nthe professor would call on somebody"},{"time":257000,"text":"to present the case."},{"time":259079,"text":"What they would do is\nthey would explain what was going on"},{"time":261880,"text":"and then dictate information\nthat the professor would transcribe"},{"time":265640,"text":"onto the many motorized blackboards\nin the front of the class,"},{"time":268569,"text":"and then we'd have a discussion."},{"time":270120,"text":"One of the really frustrating things\nis when you've done all your homework,"},{"time":274600,"text":"you come in the next day\nonly to find out that you made an error"},{"time":277640,"text":"and all of the other numbers\nyou did were wrong."},{"time":280200,"text":"And you couldn't participate as well."},{"time":282000,"text":"And we were marked by class participation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285320,"text":"So, sitting there with 87 other people\nin the class, I got to daydream a lot."},{"time":291280,"text":"Most programmers in those days\nworked on mainframes,"},{"time":295160,"text":"building things like inventory systems,\npayroll systems and bill-paying systems."},{"time":301520,"text":"But I had worked\non interactive word processing"},{"time":304040,"text":"and on-demand personal computation."},{"time":306160,"text":"Instead of thinking\nabout paper printouts and punch cards,"},{"time":310880,"text":"I imagined a magic blackboard"},{"time":313680,"text":"that if you erased one number\nand wrote a new thing in,"},{"time":317080,"text":"all of the other numbers\nwould automatically change,"},{"time":319960,"text":"like word processing with numbers."},{"time":322600,"text":"I imagined that my calculator\nhad mouse hardware on the bottom of it"},{"time":327240,"text":"and a head-up display,\nlike in a fighter plane."},{"time":330720,"text":"And I could type some numbers in,\nand circle it, and press the sum button."},{"time":334880,"text":"And right in the middle of a negotiation\nI'd be able to get the answer."},{"time":338640,"text":"Now I just had to take my fantasy\nand turn it into reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342640,"text":"My father taught me about prototyping."},{"time":345560,"text":"He showed me mock-ups"},{"time":347200,"text":"that he'd make to figure out\nthe placement on the page"},{"time":350560,"text":"for the things for brochures\nthat he was printing."},{"time":353120,"text":"And he'd use it\nto get feedback from customers"},{"time":356080,"text":"and OKs before he sent the job\noff to the presses."},{"time":360440,"text":"The act of making a simple, working\nversion of what you're trying to build"},{"time":365560,"text":"forces you to uncover key problems."},{"time":368720,"text":"And it lets you find solutions\nto those problems much less expensively."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373720,"text":"So I decided to build a prototype."},{"time":376760,"text":"I went to a video terminal connected to\nHarvard's time-sharing system"},{"time":381360,"text":"and got to work."},{"time":382880,"text":"One of the first problems\nthat I ran into was:"},{"time":386160,"text":"How do you represent values in formulas?"},{"time":389280,"text":"Let me show you what I mean."},{"time":392000,"text":"I thought that you would point somewhere,"},{"time":394200,"text":"type in some words,\nthen type in some somewhere else,"},{"time":397320,"text":"put in some numbers and some more numbers,\npoint where you want the answer."},{"time":401240,"text":"And then point to the first, press minus,\npoint to the second,"},{"time":404480,"text":"and get the result."},{"time":406360,"text":"The problem was:\nWhat should I put in the formula?"},{"time":409800,"text":"It had to be something\nthe computer knew what to put in."},{"time":412444,"text":"And if you looked at the formula,"},{"time":414160,"text":"you needed to know\nwhere on the screen it referred to."},{"time":417840,"text":"The first thing I thought was\nthe programmer way of doing it."},{"time":420760,"text":"The first time you pointed to somewhere,"},{"time":422689,"text":"the computer would ask you\nto type in a unique name."},{"time":426760,"text":"It became pretty clear pretty fast that\nthat was going to be too tedious."},{"time":430560,"text":"The computer had to automatically\nmake up the name and put it inside."},{"time":434600,"text":"So I thought, why not make it be\nthe order in which you create them?"},{"time":439480,"text":"I tried that. Value 1, value 2."},{"time":442000,"text":"Pretty quickly I saw\nthat if you had more than a few values"},{"time":444786,"text":"you'd never remember\non the screen where things were."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447320,"text":"Then I said, why not instead of\nallowing you to put values anywhere,"},{"time":452640,"text":"I'll restrict you to a grid?"},{"time":454720,"text":"Then when you pointed to a cell,"},{"time":456960,"text":"the computer could put\nthe row and column in as a name."},{"time":460640,"text":"And, if I did it like a map and put ABC\nacross the top and numbers along the side,"},{"time":466840,"text":"if you saw B7 in a formula,"},{"time":469760,"text":"you'd know exactly\nwhere it was on the screen."},{"time":472640,"text":"And if you had to type the formula\nin yourself, you'd know what to do."},{"time":477440,"text":"Restricting you to a grid\nhelped solve my problem."},{"time":481200,"text":"It also opened up new capabilities,\nlike the ability to have ranges of cells."},{"time":487360,"text":"But it wasn't too restrictive --"},{"time":488960,"text":"you could still put any value,\nany formula, in any cell."},{"time":494120,"text":"And that's the way we do it to this day,\nalmost 40 years later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499109,"text":"My friend Bob and I decided that we were\ngoing to build this product together."},{"time":502800,"text":"I did more work figuring out exactly\nhow the program was supposed to behave."},{"time":507240,"text":"I wrote a reference card\nto act as documentation."},{"time":510520,"text":"It also helped me ensure\nthat the user interface I was defining"},{"time":515320,"text":"could be explained concisely\nand clearly to regular people."},{"time":519520,"text":"Bob worked in the attic of the apartment\nhe rented in Arlington, Massachusetts."},{"time":524960,"text":"This is the inside of the attic."},{"time":528240,"text":"Bob bought time on the MIT Multics System"},{"time":531040,"text":"to write computer code\non a terminal like this."},{"time":534400,"text":"And then he would download test versions\nto a borrowed Apple II"},{"time":537920,"text":"over a phone line\nusing an acoustic coupler,"},{"time":541200,"text":"and then we would test."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542920,"text":"For one of these tests I prepared\nfor this case about the Pepsi Challenge."},{"time":548720,"text":"Print wasn't working yet,\nso I had to copy everything down."},{"time":552480,"text":"Save wasn't working,\nso every time it crashed,"},{"time":554920,"text":"I had to type in all of the formulas\nagain, over and over again."},{"time":558240,"text":"The next day in class, I raised my hand;\nI got called on, and I presented the case."},{"time":562240,"text":"I did five-year projections.\nI did all sorts of different scenarios."},{"time":565840,"text":"I aced the case.\nVisiCalc was already useful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570160,"text":"The professor said, \"How did you do it?\""},{"time":573469,"text":"Well, I didn't want to tell him\nabout our secret program."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576160,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":578200,"text":"So I said, \"I took this and added this"},{"time":580080,"text":"and multiplied by this\nand subtracted that.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":582200,"text":"He said, \"Well,\nwhy didn't you use a ratio?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":584320,"text":"I said, \"Hah! A ratio --\nthat wouldn't have been as exact!\""},{"time":587360,"text":"What I didn't say was,\n\"Divide isn't working yet.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":589960,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":593080,"text":"Eventually, though,\nwe did finish enough of VisiCalc"},{"time":596960,"text":"to be able to show it to the public."},{"time":599440,"text":"My dad printed up a sample reference card"},{"time":601440,"text":"that we could use as marketing material."}]},{"cues":[{"time":604280,"text":"In June of 1979, our publisher\nannounced VisiCalc to the world,"},{"time":610080,"text":"in a small booth at the giant National\nComputer Conference in New York City."},{"time":614800,"text":"The New York Times had\na humorous article about the conference."},{"time":619480,"text":"\"The machines perform\nwhat seem religious rites ..."},{"time":621960,"text":"Even as the believers gather,"},{"time":623365,"text":"the painters in the Coliseum sign room\nare adding to the pantheon,"},{"time":626485,"text":"carefully lettering 'VISICALC'\nin giant black on yellow."},{"time":629680,"text":"All hail VISICALC!\""},{"time":631520,"text":"(Gasp) New York Times:\n\"All hail VISICALC.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":635120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":636640,"text":"That was the last mention\nof the electronic spreadsheet"},{"time":640920,"text":"in the popular business press\nfor about two years."},{"time":644840,"text":"Most people didn't get it yet."},{"time":647000,"text":"But some did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648920,"text":"In October of 1979, we shipped VisiCalc."},{"time":653880,"text":"It came in packaging\nthat looked like this."},{"time":656720,"text":"And it looked like this\nrunning on the Apple II."},{"time":660000,"text":"And the rest, as they say, is history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662360,"text":"Now, there's an awful lot\nmore to this story,"},{"time":664480,"text":"but that'll have to wait for another day."},{"time":666560,"text":"One thing, though, Harvard remembers."},{"time":669400,"text":"Here's that classroom."},{"time":671240,"text":"They put up a plaque\nto commemorate what happened there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675640,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":684400,"text":"But it also serves as a reminder"},{"time":687360,"text":"that you, too, should take\nyour unique backgrounds, skills and needs"},{"time":692880,"text":"and build prototypes to discover\nand work out the key problems,"},{"time":698160,"text":"and through that, change the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701040,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702280,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}